WEBVTT

01:11.788 --> 01:13.999
<i>There are
only two ways to live your life.</i>

01:14.124 --> 01:16.335
<i>One is as though nothing is a miracle.</i>

01:16.460 --> 01:19.338
<i>The other is as though
everything is a miracle.</i>

01:19.922 --> 01:23.508
<i>I choose to believe the latter,
and for good reason.</i>

01:29.681 --> 01:31.016
<i>My mother is always reminding me,</i>

01:31.141 --> 01:34.019
<i>there is often more to things
than meets the eye.</i>

01:35.896 --> 01:37.522
<i>That if we can zoom out a little,</i>

01:37.648 --> 01:42.027
<i>we'll realize that life
is happening for us, not to us.</i>

02:16.061 --> 02:17.563
<i>And if we just allow it to,</i>

02:17.688 --> 02:21.024
<i>the ride can be beautiful,
awesome and fantastic.</i>

02:31.201 --> 02:33.537
<i>She never said that it would be easy.</i>

02:39.835 --> 02:44.298
<i>Look, I get it, it doesn't always seem
like rainbows and butterflies.</i>

02:47.718 --> 02:48.719
Chris.

02:51.388 --> 02:53.599
<i>It's hard to zoom out
in a moment like this.</i>

03:03.901 --> 03:06.695
<i>It's hard to believe that this
was life happening for me.</i>

03:06.820 --> 03:07.988
Chris?

03:09.740 --> 03:11.074
Chris, please wake up.

03:11.199 --> 03:12.659
<i>Or for any of us.</i>

03:24.838 --> 03:26.924
<i>It certainly didn't feel like
there could be anything good</i>

03:27.049 --> 03:28.216
<i>about this situation.</i>

03:30.719 --> 03:33.555
<i>But hang on,
I'm getting ahead of myself.</i>

03:39.269 --> 03:42.064
<i>This story really starts
years before I was even born...</i>

03:57.537 --> 03:58.789
Pressure!

03:58.914 --> 03:59.915
Here we go.

04:00.040 --> 04:03.043
<i>...with another kid
from another part of the world.</i>

04:04.086 --> 04:05.671
Safe!

04:05.796 --> 04:06.922
Back off!

04:07.047 --> 04:08.257
Come on!

04:11.009 --> 04:12.135
What about Jorge?

04:13.679 --> 04:16.264
- Does he have the wind?
- Three minutes left.

04:19.935 --> 04:20.936
Bolivar!

04:21.061 --> 04:22.521
Bolivar! Come on.

04:24.106 --> 04:27.276
You're in. I need you in midfield.
You need to put pressure on.

04:27.401 --> 04:29.778
We need a goal, OK? We need the win.
Make it happen.

04:29.903 --> 04:31.405
- OK.
- Make it happen.

04:31.530 --> 04:33.407
Let's go, boys!

04:45.586 --> 04:47.963
Yes! Push it up!

04:50.257 --> 04:51.758
Get to the middle!

05:03.979 --> 05:06.815
<i>Jorge Bolivar and I
could not have been further apart.</i>

05:06.940 --> 05:09.318
<i>I was from
a middle-class American family.</i>

05:09.443 --> 05:11.862
<i>Jorge was practically Cuban royalty.</i>

05:21.204 --> 05:23.332
<i>Who would have believed
that our lives and our families</i>

05:23.457 --> 05:26.001
<i>would come together in a way
none of us could have imagined?</i>

05:43.977 --> 05:46.063
The surgery looks to be a success.

05:46.188 --> 05:48.065
He's on his way to the ICU right now.

05:48.190 --> 05:49.191
Oh, thank God.

05:49.316 --> 05:52.819
We did have to remove
the lower lobe of his left lung.

05:52.945 --> 05:55.572
He'll still be able to breathe,
but I need to warn you,

05:55.697 --> 05:57.324
the disease is progressive.

05:57.449 --> 05:59.826
You need to prepare yourself
for the fact

05:59.952 --> 06:02.329
that your son most likely
won't make it to 20.

06:02.454 --> 06:05.207
We were told he wouldn't make it to 12.

06:05.332 --> 06:08.335
My advice is to not let him
exert himself too much.

06:08.460 --> 06:10.837
He just doesn't have the lung capacity.

06:19.012 --> 06:19.972
Papa?

06:22.432 --> 06:23.517
We're here, son.

06:23.642 --> 06:25.269
You're going to be all right.

06:26.770 --> 06:28.480
You're a fighter.

06:29.648 --> 06:31.316
I'm a fighter.

06:31.441 --> 06:32.776
You're a fighter.

06:36.613 --> 06:38.407
<i>And he</i> was a fighter.

06:38.532 --> 06:39.950
<i>He took every day as it came</i>

06:41.076 --> 06:42.411
<i>as borrowed time.</i>

06:43.287 --> 06:45.664
Hey, the phone's been ringing for you
all afternoon, George.

06:47.583 --> 06:48.792
It's from Cuba.

06:49.084 --> 06:50.002
All right.

07:06.518 --> 07:07.477
Hello?

07:07.603 --> 07:09.479
Jorge, I've been trying to reach you.

07:09.605 --> 07:11.440
<i>Papa? Is that you?</i>

07:11.565 --> 07:12.816
- Yes, Jorge.
- <i>What's going on?</i>

07:12.941 --> 07:13.817
Is everything OK?

07:13.942 --> 07:16.987
I need you to go to Miami,
to help set things up for us.

07:17.112 --> 07:18.947
- <i>When?</i>
- As soon as possible.

07:19.072 --> 07:20.616
<i>Castro is becoming...</i>

07:20.741 --> 07:21.909
unpredictable.

07:22.034 --> 07:25.495
- <i>Castro is just...</i>
- We don't know what he'll do next.

07:25.621 --> 07:28.790
Get to Miami. We'll catch up
with you as soon as we can.

07:28.916 --> 07:31.710
- OK. OK.
- <i>Revolutionary...</i>

07:31.835 --> 07:34.254
<i>This was one of those
zoom-out moments.</i>

07:34.379 --> 07:36.256
<i>Life was happening</i> for <i>Jorge.</i>

07:41.678 --> 07:44.514
Yo!

07:44.640 --> 07:45.766
What are you...

07:45.891 --> 07:49.269
No. No, no, no.
You're not playing video games.

07:49.394 --> 07:51.063
Have you seen it?
It's beautiful outside.

07:51.188 --> 07:52.314
Come on, man. Let's go.

07:52.439 --> 07:55.317
Yo, come on. We gotta get moving.
We gotta get Brian, Matt, the Douvilles.

07:55.442 --> 07:58.445
We gotta pick them up on the way.
So let's go.

07:58.570 --> 08:01.240
- And who's driving?
- Um, you are.

08:01.573 --> 08:03.575
Man, when are you gonna get
your license?

08:03.700 --> 08:06.203
Why would I do that
when I got you? Hmm?

08:08.622 --> 08:09.665
There it is!

08:10.582 --> 08:11.625
Ooh!

08:14.878 --> 08:16.004
Whoo!

08:18.799 --> 08:19.883
Yo!

08:20.008 --> 08:22.135
Yo, I got you, I got you, I got you.

08:23.262 --> 08:24.763
- You know, you know.
- Go, go, go!

08:28.559 --> 08:29.476
Whoo!

08:29.601 --> 08:31.728
Of course you'd make that shot.

08:33.146 --> 08:36.190
Yo, Chris. Chris, this isn't funny.

08:37.150 --> 08:38.569
Chris! Stop fucking around.

08:40.362 --> 08:41.572
Was that a swish?

08:41.697 --> 08:44.116
Because I think I distinctly
heard a swish right there.

08:44.241 --> 08:45.492
Ho!

08:45.617 --> 08:46.702
Whoo!

08:46.827 --> 08:48.662
- Hey!
- Huh?

08:48.787 --> 08:50.289
Mom and Dad want you home.

08:50.706 --> 08:54.793
Johnny Boy, I'm gonna enjoy this for
a minute then I'll get you in the car.

08:54.918 --> 08:56.837
Now, hot shot.

08:58.672 --> 08:59.798
Jeez, man.

09:04.261 --> 09:06.930
You should have come out
with us today, it was real fun.

09:09.725 --> 09:14.021
Or not. Everybody's entitled
to their own weekend, I suppose.

09:22.446 --> 09:23.864
You're not coming inside?

09:24.489 --> 09:25.866
I got a study session.

09:27.951 --> 09:32.331
OK. All right. Cool, cool.
Uh, good chat.

09:39.171 --> 09:43.634
Hello, dearest parents.
Your favorite son has arrived.

09:43.759 --> 09:45.010
Damn it.

09:45.719 --> 09:48.513
OK. Maybe your second-favorite son.

09:48.639 --> 09:50.224
- Hey, Mom.
- Hey, honey.

09:50.933 --> 09:52.976
I made you some sandwiches.
They're on the table.

09:53.101 --> 09:56.104
Thanks. Thank you, thank you,
thank you, thank you.

10:05.572 --> 10:06.865
Did you open this?

10:06.990 --> 10:08.283
Yeah.

10:23.632 --> 10:25.092
I'm sorry.

10:25.842 --> 10:28.428
But you did get into Loyola.

10:28.554 --> 10:31.098
I know Colin will be really happy
to have you there.

10:32.474 --> 10:34.184
Yeah. Well, I...

10:34.309 --> 10:36.228
I guess I just had this idea

10:36.353 --> 10:38.480
that John and I would go
to the same college and...

10:38.605 --> 10:40.774
do the whole roommates thing, you know?

10:40.899 --> 10:42.150
Yeah, I know.

10:43.860 --> 10:48.323
You know what? I think I'm...
I'm just gonna go downstairs.

10:48.448 --> 10:50.742
Thanks for the, uh... the food.

10:53.078 --> 10:55.038
Maybe you should have
worked harder at it.

11:03.088 --> 11:04.214
Hey.

11:05.132 --> 11:06.216
Rough one.

11:07.467 --> 11:09.386
Yeah, I don't know.
Maybe he's right.

11:12.139 --> 11:14.892
Come here. Your mom needs some love.

11:15.851 --> 11:17.644
Your mom needs some love.

11:18.353 --> 11:19.855
Aw!

11:19.980 --> 11:21.648
You know I can see
what you're doing.

11:21.773 --> 11:24.109
This is kind of obvious.

11:26.445 --> 11:28.155
I just want you to remember

11:28.280 --> 11:32.117
that when things don't work out,
there's always a reason.

11:32.242 --> 11:34.995
We just might not see it
in the moment...

11:35.120 --> 11:36.288
What's the reason?

11:36.413 --> 11:39.708
John might actually crack a smile
for once if I went to school with him?

11:39.833 --> 11:41.084
Maybe.

11:41.209 --> 11:44.254
And maybe there's something
for you at Loyola.

11:44.379 --> 11:48.508
Ah, because life is happening
<i>for</i> me, not <i>to me, right?</i>

11:48.634 --> 11:51.762
Oh! Look at my smart son
listening to his mom.

11:51.887 --> 11:55.015
Yeah. You know, when you say words,
I actually hear them, it's weird.

11:55.140 --> 11:56.433
That's very good to know.

11:57.142 --> 12:00.354
Now, I want you to call your brother
Colin and tell him the good news.

12:03.523 --> 12:04.608
Yes, ma'am.

12:10.364 --> 12:11.823
Go on, go on.

12:13.367 --> 12:15.160
- I'm kidding.
- I'll just go listen over here.

12:15.285 --> 12:16.203
Yeah, OK.

12:17.412 --> 12:18.413
Hey, man. What's up?

12:20.290 --> 12:22.000
Yeah. No, no. I'm good.

12:22.125 --> 12:24.253
Uh, look, I was just calling
to let you know

12:24.378 --> 12:28.423
that your better-looking, more talented,
smarter little brother

12:28.548 --> 12:31.385
is coming to Loyola, so get ready.

12:31.510 --> 12:32.636
<i>My mom was right.</i>

12:32.761 --> 12:34.596
<i>I had to trust that
there was a bigger reason</i>

12:34.721 --> 12:36.557
<i>things were happening
the way they were.</i>

12:38.433 --> 12:39.851
<i>And same for Jorge.</i>

12:40.269 --> 12:43.772
<i>After all, he did make it past 20,
all the way to 30.</i>

12:44.773 --> 12:47.109
<i>And he was just about
to meet his bigger reason.</i>

13:04.376 --> 13:07.212
Lunch menus. Lunch menus.

13:07.337 --> 13:10.340
- Menu?
- Yes, please.

13:11.675 --> 13:14.011
- All right.
- Is this your first flight, sir?

13:14.136 --> 13:16.930
Oh, no. It's like this every time.

13:17.806 --> 13:20.809
- Deep breaths.
- Oh, I'm trying.

13:20.934 --> 13:22.352
Trust me.

13:25.397 --> 13:26.398
Sir.

13:30.611 --> 13:34.489
Listen, is there anything I can do to
make take-off a little easier for you?

13:35.949 --> 13:37.576
You could hold my hand.

13:39.119 --> 13:41.914
It would make it a lot easier
for me to breathe

13:42.039 --> 13:43.540
if you were holding my hand.

13:53.842 --> 13:59.097
I think this might actually help.
There you go.

14:00.682 --> 14:02.100
And how's that?

14:02.226 --> 14:04.519
One small step in the right direction.

14:05.896 --> 14:08.482
- Peanuts?
- Getting warmer.

14:08.607 --> 14:11.526
Just... please.
Just... Just for take-off.

14:18.367 --> 14:22.287
So, do you have a name, in case I need
to summon a medic or something?

14:22.412 --> 14:23.830
Jorge.

14:23.956 --> 14:25.666
- Jorge.
- Yeah.

14:25.791 --> 14:28.001
Are you in Puerto Rico
for business or pleasure, Jorge?

14:28.126 --> 14:29.211
- It's business.
- Business.

14:29.336 --> 14:31.588
But it's quickly shifting to pleasure.

14:33.131 --> 14:34.841
- What kind of business?
- Rum.

14:34.967 --> 14:36.885
- Rum?
- Hm-hmm.

14:37.010 --> 14:40.097
My father wanted to make sure
that we could handle our liquor

14:40.222 --> 14:42.015
- before we went to college.
- OK.

14:42.140 --> 14:45.394
Turns out that
rum is actually my favorite.

14:45.519 --> 14:46.728
Do you have a favorite brand?

14:46.853 --> 14:49.565
Well... Bolivar, of course.

14:49.690 --> 14:52.442
OK. Well, this is...

14:52.568 --> 14:54.444
This is more than a coincidence.

14:57.072 --> 15:00.867
Oh! You work for Bolivar.

15:00.993 --> 15:03.161
Bolivar. OK.

15:05.330 --> 15:07.291
Well, you don't waste time, do you?

15:07.416 --> 15:09.084
I don't have time to waste.

15:25.017 --> 15:26.226
So you made it.

15:26.351 --> 15:27.853
I did.

15:27.978 --> 15:30.814
- I really enjoyed talking to you.
- Me too.

15:31.523 --> 15:34.401
I think I've finally got
the circulation back in my fingers.

15:34.526 --> 15:36.987
I'm so sorry about that.

15:38.071 --> 15:39.573
In Miami for long?

15:39.698 --> 15:43.827
- Uh, just tonight.
- Oh. And how can I see you again?

15:45.203 --> 15:47.414
You just like that Bolivar
is my favorite drink.

15:47.539 --> 15:50.167
Of course I do,
but how can I see you again?

15:50.292 --> 15:53.670
All right, Mr. Bolivar.

15:55.380 --> 15:57.716
Let's see if that's
just the rum talking.

16:16.902 --> 16:20.280
The most important thing
is that we do not skip a beat.

16:20.906 --> 16:21.949
What's her name?

16:25.494 --> 16:28.455
- It's the future Mrs. Jorge Bolivar.
- What?

16:29.414 --> 16:30.707
Boys!

16:31.750 --> 16:32.834
Focus!

16:34.503 --> 16:36.046
Let's get to work.

16:36.964 --> 16:40.217
As always, readings for next week
are listed in the syllabus,

16:40.342 --> 16:44.846
and a reminder that pop quizzes
make up 30 percent of your grade.

16:44.972 --> 16:46.098
Hint, hint.

16:46.223 --> 16:49.142
- Thirty percent.
- See you next week.

16:55.440 --> 16:58.151
Aw, excuse me. My bad.

16:58.277 --> 16:59.820
Thank you.

17:00.529 --> 17:02.197
Oh! I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

17:02.322 --> 17:03.949
That's my fault. I, um...

17:04.073 --> 17:07.369
I, I didn't, um...
That's... it's my fault. Um...

17:08.161 --> 17:09.663
Excuse me.

17:09.788 --> 17:11.331
Excuse me.

17:13.667 --> 17:15.293
All right. Let's get settled.

17:15.836 --> 17:17.044
Hey.

17:18.504 --> 17:20.715
Are you in this class also?

17:20.840 --> 17:22.592
Hm-hmm. Yeah.

17:23.385 --> 17:24.595
Yeah. This...

17:25.177 --> 17:26.178
Nope.

17:26.305 --> 17:28.974
No, uh... I was.

17:36.440 --> 17:38.275
I'm... I'm gonna go now.

17:38.400 --> 17:39.568
Sorry for the...

17:41.987 --> 17:43.280
Excuse me.

17:48.327 --> 17:50.621
I don't know. The dude just smells.

17:50.746 --> 17:52.164
That's roommates, man.

17:52.289 --> 17:54.082
Wait. Have you asked him about it?

17:54.207 --> 17:56.460
I'm worried he's one of those...
one of those hoarders

17:56.585 --> 17:59.087
who leaves half-eaten
chicken carcasses under his bed.

17:59.212 --> 18:02.758
- Gross. Have you checked?
- I'm scared to.

18:02.883 --> 18:05.302
The smell's so bad, though,
I'm gonna have to.

18:05.427 --> 18:06.929
Yeah. Anyway, pray for me.

18:07.054 --> 18:08.555
- Yeah. Good luck, man.
- See ya.

18:09.556 --> 18:10.599
What is he talking about?

18:10.724 --> 18:14.144
Hey, bro, you seem a little dazed.
First month of college getting to you?

18:15.854 --> 18:17.898
- I had a vision.
- Huh?

18:18.023 --> 18:21.026
- A vision.
- What's a vision, Chris?

18:23.904 --> 18:26.490
It was the most beautiful girl
that I've ever seen.

18:26.615 --> 18:28.742
Seriously, in my entire life.

18:28.867 --> 18:30.744
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

18:30.869 --> 18:33.205
You are not usually one
to get flustered about a girl.

18:33.330 --> 18:35.499
I know. But she's, like, angelic, man.

18:35.624 --> 18:38.669
It was this vision, like,
right in front of me.

18:39.670 --> 18:42.422
I gotta see her again.
I can't go to class. I gotta see her.

18:42.547 --> 18:45.133
- Hey, hey! Slow your roll, dude.
- I have to see her.

18:45.259 --> 18:48.178
- I'm serious.
- There will be plenty of girls, Chris.

18:49.346 --> 18:51.974
Not like this one, man.
Not like this one.

18:53.684 --> 18:54.768
<i>My brother was right.</i>

18:54.893 --> 18:58.146
<i>I was only a freshman,
and there would be plenty of girls.</i>

18:58.272 --> 19:01.733
<i>But she was right in front of me.</i>

19:01.858 --> 19:03.193
- Ooh!
- I'm sorry.

19:03.318 --> 19:05.237
I'm so sorry, I was lost.

19:07.322 --> 19:08.657
- You.
- You.

19:11.952 --> 19:17.249
- Safety patrol.
- Yeah. What do you think? Lame?

19:17.374 --> 19:19.918
No, not... not exactly lame.

19:20.043 --> 19:22.462
But there's no... ring to it.

19:22.588 --> 19:24.381
Well, it depends
what you're trying to say.

19:24.506 --> 19:26.758
Are you trying to say,

19:27.718 --> 19:30.429
"We, the Safety Patrol,
are here to patrol you"?

19:30.554 --> 19:33.682
Or are you trying to say, like,
"Yo! What's up, guys?

19:33.807 --> 19:35.142
We're trying to have a good time.

19:35.267 --> 19:37.144
Safety Buddy's here
to get you home safely"?

19:37.269 --> 19:40.230
All right. OK, I see your point.
It's a little too scary.

19:40.355 --> 19:41.523
Just a tad.

19:41.648 --> 19:43.483
But I need people
to know how serious this.

19:43.609 --> 19:46.612
No, absolutely, and I agree with you.
That's why I think maybe if you...

19:47.779 --> 19:49.990
change it a little bit,
people might actually...

19:50.115 --> 19:53.076
- OK.
- ...wanna join or use the service.

19:53.201 --> 19:55.579
OK. Fair point. Thank you.

19:55.704 --> 19:56.997
- These are yours.
- Yep.

19:57.122 --> 19:59.833
And I'm... I'm Chris Gregory.

19:59.958 --> 20:01.418
Hi, Chris Gregory.

20:01.543 --> 20:04.087
- Hi.
- And thank you for your input.

20:05.213 --> 20:07.257
Yeah. See, aren't you glad
you bumped into me?

20:07.382 --> 20:08.717
- Twice.
- Twice.

20:08.842 --> 20:11.887
- Hm-hmm.
- Yes. Yeah. Twice.

20:12.012 --> 20:14.890
- Samantha.
- Sam. Just Sam.

20:15.015 --> 20:16.308
Sam. Just Sam. OK.

20:16.433 --> 20:18.268
Cool. Well, Just Sam,
today's your lucky day.

20:18.393 --> 20:20.270
- You just got your first Safety Buddy.
- Really?

20:20.395 --> 20:21.438
- Yeah.
- You want to join?

20:21.563 --> 20:23.357
Definitely. I can tell
you care about it.

20:23.482 --> 20:25.067
- I do. Great.
- That's me, this guy.

20:25.192 --> 20:27.110
Then you are my first safety driver.

20:28.654 --> 20:30.155
- Ahh!
- What?

20:30.280 --> 20:31.615
See, I can't drive.

20:31.740 --> 20:34.034
- You can't drive?
- Don't have my license.

20:34.159 --> 20:35.410
- Oh.
- But I'm getting it.

20:35.535 --> 20:37.287
- Oh?
- Yes, and you're gonna help me.

20:37.412 --> 20:39.915
- I'm gonna help you?
- Until then, I'll be your ride-along.

20:40.040 --> 20:42.459
- My what?
- Yeah. Like your buddy in the side.

20:45.504 --> 20:47.798
Why do I have this feeling
like I'm getting conned into something?

20:47.923 --> 20:51.051
Because you are. But it's gonna
work out for you in the end.

20:51.176 --> 20:53.971
- Is it?
