that this was what you wanted to do?

36:44.671 --> 36:45.714
Uh...

36:46.423 --> 36:48.216
Well, um...

36:48.342 --> 36:51.470
there's actually a personal tie for me.

36:52.179 --> 36:54.181
I'll preface it with this.

36:54.306 --> 36:56.767
She's fine, thank God.

36:57.768 --> 36:58.727
But, um...

37:00.771 --> 37:03.857
Two years ago, my mom
was almost killed in a car accident.

37:03.982 --> 37:06.944
She was driving to pick me
and my brother up from the airport

37:07.069 --> 37:09.446
when some guy

37:09.571 --> 37:12.074
coming home from a late night
crossed over the center divider

37:12.199 --> 37:13.450
and hit her head on.

37:14.534 --> 37:19.706
And she went into a coma and...
we didn't know if she was gonna make it.

37:21.708 --> 37:24.920
We were sitting there waiting
and it just felt like forever.

37:25.045 --> 37:28.632
And while praying for her to wake up,
I made a deal with the big guy,

37:28.757 --> 37:30.551
that if she was OK,

37:32.010 --> 37:35.347
then I would do whatever I could
to make sure other people stayed safe.

37:35.847 --> 37:37.933
And so, here we are.

37:41.979 --> 37:43.146
Wow.

37:46.108 --> 37:47.317
That's a, uh...

37:48.151 --> 37:50.279
That's a pretty deep layer, Sam.

37:50.404 --> 37:51.613
Hmm.

37:52.364 --> 37:54.074
I think she's beautiful.

37:54.866 --> 37:56.159
You two are beautiful.

38:04.418 --> 38:05.711
<i>Surfer dude was right.</i>

38:06.795 --> 38:10.090
<i>It is beautiful when you find a cause
that you're passionate about.</i>

38:11.550 --> 38:13.802
- That's good.
- Not in front of your face.

38:13.927 --> 38:15.762
- Over there?
- I'm the safest-looking.

38:18.348 --> 38:20.851
<i>Or that person that you're really into.</i>

38:24.563 --> 38:25.939
What?

38:27.566 --> 38:29.359
I didn't know you were coming.

38:30.485 --> 38:31.653
How are you?

38:36.491 --> 38:39.286
- You're doing it.
- OK.

38:39.411 --> 38:41.413
OK, go go, go, go!

38:44.124 --> 38:45.334
- Guinea...
- Try this.

38:45.459 --> 38:46.376
Guinea pig?

38:48.086 --> 38:51.173
<i>The person that lights you up
and you would travel anywhere for.</i>

38:52.799 --> 38:54.343
You don't need to take it on and off.

38:54.468 --> 38:57.763
I'm trying! The car takes itself
where it wants to go, it's not me.

39:01.767 --> 39:05.229
<i>That person that helps make life
so much sweeter than it already is.</i>

39:06.230 --> 39:09.733
<i>The one that makes
the ordinary extraordinary.</i>

39:11.985 --> 39:14.446
<i>And makes you do things
you wouldn't normally do.</i>

39:14.571 --> 39:18.951
<i>And avoid some of the things
that you're supposed to do.</i>

39:24.164 --> 39:25.123
Dad.

39:27.251 --> 39:28.710
Three Cs and a D.

39:28.835 --> 39:31.838
You know, it's not actually
what it looks like, because, um...

39:31.964 --> 39:34.633
Do you realize you're on the verge
of flunking out of your first term?

39:34.758 --> 39:36.009
Flunking's a strong word.

39:36.134 --> 39:38.220
And don't even get me started
on your phone bill.

39:39.012 --> 39:42.391
You... You were young
and in love once, right, Dad?

39:42.516 --> 39:45.060
- Chris.
- I'm just having fun, Dad.

39:45.185 --> 39:48.564
- Hey, I am serious.
- So am I. It's responsible fun.

39:48.689 --> 39:52.025
Get your grades up,
or no more support from us.

39:54.069 --> 39:58.991
- You hear me?
- Yeah. Loud and clear. Got you.

40:03.954 --> 40:05.289
Papa.

40:05.414 --> 40:07.332
You wanted to see me?

40:07.457 --> 40:08.792
Sit.

40:13.171 --> 40:14.548
Jorge...

40:17.634 --> 40:19.177
What is going on with you?

40:21.138 --> 40:22.931
Flying all over the place.

40:24.349 --> 40:27.144
- Who is this American girl?
- You know her name.

40:28.645 --> 40:31.690
- I don't think this is a good idea.
- You don't think she's worthy?

40:31.815 --> 40:34.484
- Of course not.
- She's a <i>gringa,</i> is that it?

40:34.610 --> 40:35.986
I never said that.

40:36.111 --> 40:38.155
- You don't approve.
- Stop putting words in my mouth!

40:38.280 --> 40:40.449
So she's an American, so what?

40:40.574 --> 40:43.785
I went to Stanford.
We live in Miami, for heaven's sake.

40:57.758 --> 40:58.717
Your health.

41:00.969 --> 41:02.137
Does she know?

41:03.555 --> 41:04.556
She knows.

41:20.155 --> 41:22.783
- Hi.
- Morning.

41:23.450 --> 41:26.078
- Am I snoring?
- No.

41:26.203 --> 41:27.663
Am I?

41:31.333 --> 41:32.334
I love you.

41:33.252 --> 41:34.294
What?

41:35.128 --> 41:37.172
I love every ounce of you.

41:38.382 --> 41:39.549
Me too.

41:40.717 --> 41:42.719
You know, I've been doing
a lot of thinking.

41:44.888 --> 41:46.807
And I want to spend more time together.

41:49.851 --> 41:52.896
I just wish we lived in the same city.

41:53.021 --> 41:54.898
I mean a lot more time.

41:59.278 --> 42:00.696
- What is that?
- What?

42:02.114 --> 42:03.282
What is it?

42:10.789 --> 42:13.041
- Will you marry me?
- Oh, my goodness.

42:14.376 --> 42:15.877
Be my wife?

42:16.878 --> 42:21.675
- What about your father and your...
- No, this is about us. <i>I</i> love you.

42:21.800 --> 42:24.136
I don't see my life without you.

42:26.013 --> 42:28.473
So, please marry me.

42:29.433 --> 42:30.559
Oh, my goodness.

42:31.894 --> 42:33.395
I love you so much.

42:35.397 --> 42:36.440
Yes.

42:45.365 --> 42:46.909
What do you think of this?

42:48.452 --> 42:50.787
"Dear Dad,
I want to thank you and Mom

42:50.913 --> 42:53.874
for giving me the chance to come back
and give it another shot.

42:53.999 --> 42:57.252
I feel like I'm finally getting
this college thing right

42:57.377 --> 42:59.796
and I'm taking full advantage
of this opportunity."

43:00.339 --> 43:01.298
Miss. Miss, hi.

43:01.423 --> 43:04.635
<i>"I'm so thankful for how patient
you both have been over the years..."</i>

43:04.760 --> 43:06.637
"...and that I have parents
who believe in me

43:06.762 --> 43:08.639
even when I didn't believe in myself."

43:08.764 --> 43:09.765
Hmm.

43:09.890 --> 43:12.601
"Thank you so much for all of this."

43:12.726 --> 43:15.062
"I love you. Chris."

43:18.148 --> 43:20.442
This is code
for the new girlfriend, isn't it?

43:21.401 --> 43:23.904
- Probably.
- Yeah.

43:27.658 --> 43:28.700
You did good.

43:38.293 --> 43:40.712
OK, Just Sam,
it's the moment of truth.

43:40.837 --> 43:43.006
Yep. It's a big moment. You ready?

43:43.131 --> 43:44.841
Kind of nervous.

43:45.259 --> 43:46.260
Organ donor?

43:46.385 --> 43:48.929
Yeah. Why not? I'm not gonna
need it when I'm gone, right?

43:49.054 --> 43:50.639
Yeah, I guess not.

43:50.764 --> 43:52.140
Mr. Chris Gregory.

43:52.683 --> 43:55.352
- That's you.
- That's me. Yes. One second.

43:55.477 --> 43:57.938
- One second, I'm sorry.
- What are you doing?

43:58.063 --> 44:00.566
If I pass, you have to go
on a date with me.

44:00.691 --> 44:04.444
- What?
- Just say yes. Please. Please.

44:07.072 --> 44:09.074
- Uh, yes.
- Yes, yes.

44:09.199 --> 44:10.534
- Yes, yes!
- Yes?

44:10.659 --> 44:11.743
- Yes!
- Lovely.

44:11.868 --> 44:12.869
Yes.

44:15.539 --> 44:19.918
- Wow. You really went all out, huh?
- Yeah.

44:20.043 --> 44:22.588
I don't know, I figure
we got a lot to celebrate.

44:22.713 --> 44:24.840
- My newfound freedom.
- Hm-hmm.

44:24.965 --> 44:28.302
- Your almost graduation.
- Yeah.

44:29.052 --> 44:31.597
The fact that this is
our first official date.

44:33.056 --> 44:34.349
Yeah, I guess you're right.

44:34.474 --> 44:36.810
The celebrations do warrant the effort.

44:36.935 --> 44:39.229
- Yeah. Of course they do.
- Hm-hmm.

44:40.022 --> 44:42.858
So, what are you going to do
with your newfound liberation?

44:42.983 --> 44:45.611
You know what? I think I'm...

44:47.362 --> 44:49.698
I'm going to enjoy this date with you.

44:51.867 --> 44:53.827
I mean, in life.

44:53.952 --> 44:55.412
Oh.

44:55.537 --> 44:57.748
Like, you know,
have you thought about it?

44:57.873 --> 44:59.875
- About what?
- Life.

45:00.000 --> 45:03.211
- Oh. Life.
- You know, like future life.

45:03.337 --> 45:05.297
Oh. No, absolutely not.

45:06.089 --> 45:08.008
- Chris, seriously.
- What?

45:08.133 --> 45:09.635
Seriously. Have you thought about it?

45:09.760 --> 45:11.386
I don't know, I just, um...

45:11.511 --> 45:14.223
I like living in this moment
here with you.

45:14.348 --> 45:17.100
I don't wanna think ahead
or behind, you know?

45:17.226 --> 45:20.020
Yeah, I guess.

45:21.855 --> 45:23.690
I do really like helping people.

45:23.815 --> 45:26.777
I like seeing people happy.
It makes me happy, so...

45:27.319 --> 45:29.279
maybe something
along the lines of that.

45:29.404 --> 45:30.322
- You know.
- Hm-hmm.

45:30.447 --> 45:33.283
Use these good looks and charm
to save the world.

45:34.618 --> 45:35.619
Wow.

45:36.078 --> 45:38.288
My mom's studying to be a nurse, but...

45:39.790 --> 45:44.127
She's like... a really special person.

45:44.253 --> 45:49.174
I don't really think that I've got what
it takes, you know, to help people.

45:49.299 --> 45:51.718
I mean, I definitely
can't save somebody's life.

45:51.843 --> 45:53.053
I don't know.

45:54.096 --> 45:56.014
You've been a pretty amazing
Safety Buddy.

45:56.139 --> 45:57.516
- Oh.
- Hm-hmm.

45:57.641 --> 45:58.934
Is that so? Amazing?

45:59.059 --> 46:00.477
- Yeah.
- I'm amazing.

46:00.602 --> 46:01.687
Chris Gregory's amazing.

46:01.812 --> 46:03.480
I mean, it comes very naturally to you.

46:03.605 --> 46:05.190
Oh. So I'm a natural.

46:05.315 --> 46:07.067
- I'm naturally amazing.
- Oh.

46:07.192 --> 46:09.945
- I'm naturally amazing.
- Oh, my gosh. You are so annoying.

46:10.070 --> 46:12.447
I'm not! This is going better
than I thought it was going to go.

46:12.573 --> 46:14.575
- My gosh. Shut up.
- This is great for me.

46:15.325 --> 46:17.995
This is going so well that you
might have to meet my family

46:18.120 --> 46:20.038
when they come for the Easter break.

46:20.289 --> 46:22.332
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

47:24.645 --> 47:26.188
Whoo!

47:29.942 --> 47:31.818
- There it is!
- Get it, get it!

47:34.488 --> 47:36.907
- Wow.
- What is... What's happening?

47:37.032 --> 47:38.659
Oh, my gosh.

47:38.784 --> 47:41.328
- What is happening?
- Whoo!

47:41.453 --> 47:42.996
I miss my boys!

47:43.121 --> 47:46.833
Oh, you mean you miss Chris and I
dominating John and Dad?

47:47.417 --> 47:49.086
I wouldn't be too quick
to say that, Col.

47:49.211 --> 47:50.796
All right, got Old Man Winkle.

47:53.215 --> 47:55.467
- I got Dad, I got Dad.
- Someone's gonna get hurt!

47:59.680 --> 48:01.765
Are you sure you can handle this?

48:01.890 --> 48:03.100
I have a brother.

48:03.225 --> 48:05.894
No, I mean Chris.
He can be a handful.

48:06.019 --> 48:07.563
Hmm, I think I can handle it.

48:07.688 --> 48:11.316
- You. Man, what's going on with you?
- Looking thin.

48:11.441 --> 48:14.653
By the way, guys,
uh, take a look at this.

48:16.280 --> 48:17.281
What is that?

48:17.823 --> 48:20.158
Oh! You wanna see it?
OK, I'm sorry.

48:21.952 --> 48:24.121
Look, read it... and weep.

48:24.246 --> 48:26.290
- Wow, only took you three years.
- Thank you.

48:26.415 --> 48:28.083
His girlfriend was a big motivation.

48:28.208 --> 48:30.836
I mean, and I even survived
all the lessons, so...

48:30.961 --> 48:32.045
Oh, thanks. Thank you.

48:32.170 --> 48:33.839
- I'm impressed.
- Congratulations.

48:33.964 --> 48:35.841
- That's great.
- How many times did it take?

48:35.966 --> 48:38.468
- Actually, once.
- Let's eat. Come on.

48:38.594 --> 48:40.888
"How many times did it take?"
"It took him three times."

48:41.013 --> 48:43.140
"How many times did it take
to get your license, Chris?"

48:45.976 --> 48:47.269
Behave yourself, OK?

48:47.394 --> 48:49.021
- Yeah, of course. Always.
- I love you.

48:51.231 --> 48:52.482
- This is for you.
- What is this?

48:52.608 --> 48:53.692
- It's a little...
- What? No.

48:53.817 --> 48:56.153
- Take it.
- I don't need your money.

48:56.278 --> 48:57.446
Thanks, Mom.

48:58.280 --> 48:59.156
Mommy.

49:00.657 --> 49:01.783
- Love you.
- Love you, too.

49:01.909 --> 49:03.535
- Take care of your brother.
- I'll try.

49:06.038 --> 49:07.789
Drive safely.

49:07.915 --> 49:09.333
There you go. I love you.

49:10.000 --> 49:11.084
- Bye.
- Bye.

49:13.086 --> 49:14.963
Lovely meeting you.

49:15.088 --> 49:16.298
Thank you.

49:20.093 --> 49:21.428
Thanks for everything, Pop.

49:23.347 --> 49:24.389
I love you.

49:26.099 --> 49:27.809
- Keep your grades up.
- Yeah.

49:30.145 --> 49:31.063
Hear that?

49:31.605 --> 49:33.023
- Have fun.
- Yes.

49:33.148 --> 49:34.816
- Not too much fun.
- Of course not.

49:34.942 --> 49:36.610
- Be good.
- Always.

49:36.735 --> 49:38.278
Bye.

49:38.654 --> 49:39.655
I love you.

49:39.780 --> 49:41.281
- I love you more.
- Love you.

49:41.406 --> 49:42.950
- Bye.
- Oh, my gosh!

49:44.660 --> 49:46.495
Wait! Come back!

49:46.620 --> 49:48.247
Don't leave me!

49:50.832 --> 49:52.167
<i>That was a very good day.</i>

50:10.686 --> 50:12.521
I, Jorge Bolivar...

50:12.646 --> 50:14.523
I, Leslie Folk...

50:14.648 --> 50:16.191
...take you, Leslie Folk...

50:16.316 --> 50:19.319
...take you, Jorge Bolivar...

50:19.444 --> 50:21.071
...to be my lawfully wedded wife...

50:21.196 --> 50:23.198
...to be my lawfully wedded husband...

50:23.323 --> 50:24.700
...for better or for worse...

50:24.825 --> 50:27.160
...for better or for worse...

50:27.286 --> 50:29.329
...in sickness and in health...

50:30.247 --> 50:32.124
...in sickness and in health...

50:33.208 --> 50:34.710
...as long as we both shall live.

50:36.336 --> 50:38.463
...as long as we both shall live.

51:09.828 --> 51:10.871
My wife?

51:14.249 --> 51:15.542
My husband.

51:16.501 --> 51:18.629
Cheers.

51:22.758 --> 51:24.468
What a day, right?

51:24.593 --> 51:27.221
- It was bliss.
- Yeah.

51:28.680 --> 51:30.432
I'm sorry your parents weren't here.

51:30.557 --> 51:33.977
No. Don't be. We don't need the drama.

51:36.313 --> 51:39.858
Today was about us
and our life together.

51:41.026 --> 51:43.237
They'll fall in love with you
just like I did.

51:43.362 --> 51:45.197
Do you promise?

51:46.823 --> 51:48.075
I promise.

51:48.867 --> 51:51.662
My little peanut.

51:56.792 --> 51:57.709
OK.

51:59.419 --> 52:00.504
OK.

52:01.255 --> 52:02.756
You're doing this?

52:02.881 --> 52:06.009
I think it's about time we start
working on those dozens of babies

52:06.134 --> 52:07.594
you've been talking about.

52:07.719 --> 52:09.346
Whoo!

52:09.471 --> 52:12.599
How did I get to be this lucky, huh?
Whoo!

52:27.072 --> 52:28.907
You're almost
getting out of here, Sam.

52:29.032 --> 52:30.909
- Yeah.
- Got any plans after graduation?

52:31.577 --> 52:34.204
Probably intern
at this nonprofit that I like.

52:34.329 --> 52:36.999
Yeah, that's right, my girl's smart.

52:37.124 --> 52:39.167
- Any of that rub off on you?
- Ho-ho!

52:39.293 --> 52:42.796
Yes, actually. I'm thinking about
signing up for the fire department.

52:42.921 --> 52:46.383
- You just wanna play with the siren.
- Yeah, one hundred percent.

52:46.508 --> 52:48.010
Have you heard that thing? Whoo-ooh!

52:48.135 --> 52:50.554
And then hopefully some traveling
at some point, right?

52:50.679 --> 52:53.307
- Yeah, traveling would be real nice.
- Hm-hmm.

52:53.432 --> 52:54.474
- I can see it.
- Whoa!

52:54.600 --> 52:57.144
Blue ocean, me and you, a yacht

52:57.269 --> 52:59.229
just like this. I'm standing here

52:59.354 --> 53:00.898
and you're holding me across my chest

53:01.023 --> 53:03.442
and there's all these tropical fish
and...

53:03.984 --> 53:05.944
all this amazing...

53:07.321 --> 53:11.074
Ignore him. He does this way too often.
Chris, dude, cut it out.

53:11.199 --> 53:12.284
Yeah, Chris.

53:13.035 --> 53:14.953
- Chris!
- Chris, the joke is over.

53:15.579 --> 53:17.748
Why isn't he stopping? Chris?
What's happening?

53:17.873 --> 53:19.374
- Chris!
- Hey!

53:19.499 --> 53:21.168
- Chris!
- Chris! Wake up, Chris!

53:21.293 --> 53:22.753
- Come on, hey!
- Stop kidding around!

53:22.878 --> 53:25.464
Oh, God. Hey, go grab your car!
Go get your car!

53:26.131 --> 53:27.049
Come on, big guy.

53:28.050 --> 53:29.968
Come on, stay with us.

53:31.803 --> 53:33.013
OK, come on.

53:34.598 --> 53:35.599
Chris!

53:36.308 --> 53:37.559
Chris.

53:40.520 --> 53:41.647
No!

53:57.871 --> 53:59.039
Doctor.

54:00.415 --> 54:04.503
The MRI shows bleeding
in the frontal lobe of your son's brain.

54:04.628 --> 54:05.921
There is no sign of trauma,

54:06.046 --> 54:09.007
so it's possible he may have
some type of aneurism

54:09.132 --> 54:11.969
or a bleeding arterial
venous malformation.

54:15.138 --> 54:16.640
Please.

54:16.765 --> 54:18.350
Please don't leave me.

54:19.059 --> 54:20.894
I love you so much.

54:21.812 --> 54:23.313
Please.

54:23.438 --> 54:24.940
Please come back to me.

54:32.030 --> 54:33.240
Sam.

54:33.782 --> 54:35.367
Chris? Chris?

54:35.492 --> 54:38.036
John. John.

54:38.161 --> 54:40.289
Chris? You guys.

54:42.207 --> 54:43.834
- Hey.
- Chris.

54:43.959 --> 54:45.752
Are you good?

54:47.379 --> 54:49.673
I've never felt better, actually.

54:51.550 --> 54:53.260
And that's saying something.

54:54.177 --> 54:55.429
Yeah, he's better, all right.

54:56.430 --> 54:57.973
We thought we lost you.

54:58.098 --> 54:59.600
I had this dream

55:00.517 --> 55:03.604
that I was this caterpillar
trapped in a cocoon.

55:04.980 --> 55:07.024
It was really, really dark inside.

55:08.025 --> 55:10.736
I kept scratching the cocoon,
trying to get out,

55:10.861 --> 55:11.987
but I couldn't get out.

55:12.112 --> 55:14.448
It was like I was stuck,
like I couldn't move my body.

55:14.573 --> 55:16.325
I was so scared.

55:17.659 --> 55:19.870
I didn't think that I
was gonna make it home.

55:20.996 --> 55:22.956
Then I heard your voice.

55:25.125 --> 55:26.960
I started to see like a...

55:27.586 --> 55:30.672
like a light, and I started
to see this way out.

55:32.758 --> 55:37.971
And then... I realized that I was
more than I ever thought I was...

55:39.264 --> 55:43.268
That I was like
this beautiful butterfly.

55:45.896 --> 55:47.814
And I could just fly.

55:48.899 --> 55:51.485
Was there a little dog
named Toto there, too?

55:52.277 --> 55:53.779
A wicked witch?

55:54.404 --> 55:57.115
Yeah. Yeah, there was.

55:57.241 --> 55:58.951
And the witch was your wife.

56:00.869 --> 56:02.829
Hey, your brother
just got out of a coma.

56:02.955 --> 56:04.039
Don't beat him up.

56:05.290 --> 56:08.293
Well, I'm just glad
that you didn't fly away.

56:09.544 --> 56:10.462
Me too.

56:12.923 --> 56:14.299
Careful, careful.

56:16.426 --> 56:19.638
Because there's actually something
that I wanted to ask you.

56:44.997 --> 56:45.998
- Hi.
- Hi.

56:48.166 --> 56:49.167
Dearly beloved,

56:49.293 --> 56:52.462
we are gathered here today
to witness this man, Christopher,

56:52.588 --> 56:55.674
marry this woman, Sam,
in holy matrimony.

56:57.718 --> 56:59.511
You look amazing.

57:00.053 --> 57:01.305
You, too.

57:04.141 --> 57:05.350
Chris.

57:06.143 --> 57:08.061
Oh, um...

57:09.938 --> 57:13.317
I, Chris, take you, Sam,

57:14.276 --> 57:16.236
to be my lawfully wedded wife.

57:19.114 --> 57:23.911
And I, Sam, take you, Chris,
to be my husband.

57:24.369 --> 57:27.331
To have and to hold, this day forward...

57:28.040 --> 57:30.334
...as long as we both shall live.

57:31.793 --> 57:33.337
By the power vested in me,

57:33.462 --> 57:35.589
I now pronounce you husband and wife.

57:36.214 --> 57:38.175
Chris, you may kiss your bride.

58:16.255 --> 58:19.591
<i>Just like that,
the future life Sam talked about</i>

58:19.716 --> 58:21.093
<i>began to come into focus.</i>

59:03.677 --> 59:04.887
<i>It wasn't all that different</i>

59:05.012 --> 59:08.140
<i>from the life that Jorge and Leslie
were living years before.</i>

59:08.265 --> 59:12.102
<i>Moving together by similarity,
separated by time.</i>

59:22.988 --> 59:26.950
Straight away. Close the door.
Home, sweet home.

59:27.075 --> 59:28.785
- I got it.
- You got it?

59:29.494 --> 59:34.541
Home, sweet home, look at it.
Nice, huh? The kitchen.

59:34.666 --> 59:35.667
- Hm-hmm.
- Like it?

59:35.792 --> 59:37.336
- I do.
- Hm-hmm?

59:37.461 --> 59:39.004
Hm-hmm.

59:39.129 --> 59:42.966
You know, there are a couple
of empty rooms to fill.

1:00:24.841 --> 1:00:27.594
<i>But there were some differences
in how our lives played out.</i>

1:00:31.139 --> 1:00:32.724
<i>Painful differences.</i>

1:00:47.656 --> 1:00:49.074
Did you get the job?

1:00:51.410 --> 1:00:53.120
Oh, I knew you would.

1:00:54.913 --> 1:00:56.206
I'm so proud of you.

1:00:56.331 --> 1:00:59.793
- Thank you, thank you.
- Aw!

1:01:00.419 --> 1:01:02.879
- You like the shirt?
- Yes. It's a nice shirt.

1:01:03.005 --> 1:01:04.089
- All right?
- Yeah.

1:01:04.214 --> 1:01:06.049
Yeah, we're gonna be
making the big bucks now,

1:01:06.174 --> 1:01:08.343
so we can make
a couple of changes around here.

1:01:08.468 --> 1:01:11.388
Maybe starting with a shower
I can actually fit in.

1:01:11.513 --> 1:01:14.016
Actually, I think
the first thing we should do

1:01:14.141 --> 1:01:17.102
is put some paint in that front bedroom.

1:01:17.227 --> 1:01:18.604
OK. Yeah, what color?

1:01:18.729 --> 1:01:19.855
Daddy.

1:01:20.272 --> 1:01:22.232
Dad?

1:01:22.357 --> 1:01:23.317
- Hm-hmm.
- Me?

1:01:23.442 --> 1:01:24.484
- Hm-hmm.
- No.

1:01:24.610 --> 1:01:25.777
- Hm-hmm.
- No.

1:01:25.903 --> 1:01:26.862
- Yeah.
- No.

1:01:26.987 --> 1:01:28.322
- No, you're lying.
- Yes. Yes!

1:01:28.447 --> 1:01:30.616
Yes? Oh!

1:01:32.117 --> 1:01:33.368
- What?
- Yes.

1:01:33.493 --> 1:01:35.495
No, I can't.

1:01:36.079 --> 1:01:37.247
Wow.

1:01:38.206 --> 1:01:40.334
Wow, wow, wow.

1:01:40.459 --> 1:01:41.835
- You...?
- Hm-hmm.

1:01:44.630 --> 1:01:46.089
I can't believe it.

1:01:46.715 --> 1:01:47.883
I can't believe it.

1:01:48.008 --> 1:01:49.551
It's crazy.

1:01:52.888 --> 1:01:55.182
- I love you.
- I love you.

1:02:05.943 --> 1:02:08.070
- Is that its...
- No.

1:02:08.195 --> 1:02:10.113
No, that's the umbilical cord.

1:02:11.865 --> 1:02:13.450
Yeah, of course it is.

1:02:17.871 --> 1:02:20.874
I received your results
and I reviewed them,

1:02:20.999 --> 1:02:23.502
and I wish I could give you
better news, but...

1:02:23.627 --> 1:02:27.756
given your medical history,
we're not very optimistic.

1:02:29.675 --> 1:02:32.052
I'm sorry.

1:02:32.177 --> 1:02:35.430
OK. Well, thank you for your time.

1:02:57.369 --> 1:03:00.455
You know, it's my fault.
You never should have married me.

1:03:00.581 --> 1:03:02.165
We don't know that.

1:03:03.959 --> 1:03:05.794
I can't give you what you want.

1:03:05.919 --> 1:03:08.005
I can't give you what you deserve.

1:03:09.423 --> 1:03:10.382
No, my love.

1:03:10.507 --> 1:03:12.843
You said you wanted a big family.

1:03:12.968 --> 1:03:14.803
With dozens and dozens.

1:03:16.930 --> 1:03:18.515
Dozens of babies.

1:03:22.561 --> 1:03:23.979
I failed you.

1:03:27.190 --> 1:03:28.400
Listen to me.

1:03:30.152 --> 1:03:31.653
You're my family.

1:03:32.613 --> 1:03:35.866
You're all I ever wanted
and you're all I need.

1:03:37.451 --> 1:03:39.870
You're the best thing
that ever happened to me.

1:03:40.996 --> 1:03:44.416
And I wouldn't change any of it.

1:03:48.045 --> 1:03:49.463
I'm sorry.

1:03:51.006 --> 1:03:52.466
I'm so sorry.

1:03:58.555 --> 1:04:02.142
Everyone grab your bolster
and find a comfortable seat.

1:04:04.186 --> 1:04:08.190
Now let's close our eyes,
put our hands on our bellies,

1:04:08.315 --> 1:04:11.902
and visualize the connection
to the life within.

1:04:27.042 --> 1:04:28.460
<i>Tío!</i>

1:04:30.796 --> 1:04:31.755
<i>Tío!</i>

1:04:36.593 --> 1:04:38.303
He's getting worse, isn't he?

1:04:40.973 --> 1:04:43.350
We want to make
the most of every moment.

1:04:53.944 --> 1:04:55.737
To the Aliento de Vida.

1:04:58.115 --> 1:04:59.408
The Breath of Life.

1:05:09.376 --> 1:05:12.379
We're gonna take off.
Thank you, guys, for coming.

1:05:13.755 --> 1:05:16.133
He's so perfect.

1:05:16.884 --> 1:05:18.135
I love you so much.

1:05:23.056 --> 1:05:25.183
Hi. Is that Mom?

1:05:33.567 --> 1:05:36.904
OK, we should really go back to shore.

1:05:39.573 --> 1:05:40.574
No.

1:05:41.325 --> 1:05:43.035
Listen, we want you
feeling well, my love.

1:05:43.160 --> 1:05:46.163
No. No, I don't want
anybody worrying about me.

1:05:52.794 --> 1:05:55.005
<i>Tío! Tío,</i> come in!

1:05:57.382 --> 1:05:58.717
Oh! Jorge!

1:06:00.761 --> 1:06:03.764
No. Check his oxygen. OK, I got you.

1:06:03.889 --> 1:06:06.642
Uncle Jorge's gonna be OK. It's OK.

1:06:08.435 --> 1:06:09.436
It's OK.

1:06:14.441 --> 1:06:16.652
I have been in touch
with the Mayo Clinic.

1:06:16.777 --> 1:06:20.072
I'm making arrangements for you
to be screened for a transplant.

1:06:21.531 --> 1:06:22.783
A transplant?

1:06:22.908 --> 1:06:25.786
Without new lungs,
I don't see him lasting another year,

1:06:25.911 --> 1:06:27.621
maybe not even another month.

1:06:27.746 --> 1:06:29.122
To qualify for the procedure,

1:06:29.248 --> 1:06:32.000
you need to be sick enough
where you need it, which you clearly do,

1:06:32.125 --> 1:06:34.836
but healthy enough
to survive the procedure.

1:06:35.671 --> 1:06:37.005
Well, that's good.

1:06:51.353 --> 1:06:52.854
I thought you were sleeping.

1:06:55.774 --> 1:06:57.192
Too many thoughts.

1:06:59.778 --> 1:07:01.905
You should be in bed, my love.

1:07:06.159 --> 1:07:08.328
I have something for you, Peanut.

1:07:09.121 --> 1:07:13.625
<i>♪ Happy birthday to you</i>

1:07:15.836 --> 1:07:20.340
<i>♪ Happy birthday to you</i>

1:07:22.426 --> 1:07:27.264
<i>♪ Happy birthday, dear Peanut...</i>

1:07:27.389 --> 1:07:30.350
Shh! No, it's not for another month.

1:07:33.645 --> 1:07:36.523
<i>♪ Happy birthday</i>

1:07:36.648 --> 1:07:38.483
<i>♪ To you</i>

1:07:40.152 --> 1:07:41.361
Peanut.

1:07:44.323 --> 1:07:46.533
In case, hmm?

1:07:47.159 --> 1:07:49.828
Shh! Shh!

1:08:00.756 --> 1:08:02.257
- Get it, buddy!
- Yay!

1:08:03.717 --> 1:08:05.802
- What is it?
- What is it?

1:08:05.928 --> 1:08:07.638
Is that a truck?

1:08:07.763 --> 1:08:09.389
It's a fire truck.

1:08:09.514 --> 1:08:11.850
Thank you, Uncle Colin and Uncle John.

1:08:25.072 --> 1:08:26.281
Hello?

1:08:26.406 --> 1:08:27.616
Yes.

1:08:29.159 --> 1:08:30.577
Dr. Keller?

1:08:31.578 --> 1:08:32.954
Tonight?

1:08:35.040 --> 1:08:37.542
Oh, yes, yes, I can arrange that.

1:08:38.126 --> 1:08:42.047
All right, well, I'll call you.
Thank you. Thank you very much.

1:08:42.172 --> 1:08:43.215
Oh, my Lord.

1:08:46.842 --> 1:08:48.345
You're not gonna believe this.

1:08:49.887 --> 1:08:51.640
They have a donor for you.

1:08:52.975 --> 1:08:55.060
Jorge, are you all right?

1:08:55.185 --> 1:08:58.438
Because we need to get you
to the clinic as soon as possible.

1:08:59.398 --> 1:09:00.732
Come here.

1:09:02.650 --> 1:09:05.988
I've lived a good life, haven't I?

1:09:06.572 --> 1:09:07.698
What are you saying?

1:09:07.823 --> 1:09:09.949
This doesn't make any sense.

1:09:10.492 --> 1:09:12.911
Should go to someone younger.

1:09:13.036 --> 1:09:14.579
Just, please, stop.

1:09:14.704 --> 1:09:16.873
Someone more deserving.

1:09:17.623 --> 1:09:19.458
I love my life.

1:09:20.127 --> 1:09:22.337
I've been blessed and had so...

1:09:23.171 --> 1:09:24.797
I've had so much.

1:09:27.259 --> 1:09:28.217
I've had you,

1:09:28.342 --> 1:09:29.927
my family.

1:09:30.052 --> 1:09:34.224
Maybe we should go onto the Aliento,

1:09:34.349 --> 1:09:36.226
let whatever happens happen.

1:09:36.351 --> 1:09:41.230
My darling, this is your chance
to finally breathe again.

1:09:41.690 --> 1:09:44.610
And I am right here by your side.

1:09:45.402 --> 1:09:47.362
But you will need to fight again.

1:09:47.487 --> 1:09:50.114
And if you don't fight for yourself,

1:09:50.239 --> 1:09:53.327
I need you to fight for me.

1:09:56.246 --> 1:09:57.497
We can do this.

1:10:00.584 --> 1:10:02.502
That's it, that's it.

1:10:02.628 --> 1:10:04.087
OK.

1:10:04.963 --> 1:10:06.965
- Great.
- Thank you.

1:10:10.886 --> 1:10:15.057
So, Dr. Keller is on his way
to get the lungs.

1:10:15.182 --> 1:10:18.227
You make it sound like
the UPS delivery service.

1:10:21.688 --> 1:10:24.983
You know, this reminds me
of the first time we met.

1:10:28.278 --> 1:10:30.656
I'd feel a lot better
if you hold my hand.

1:10:33.867 --> 1:10:35.535
Always a charmer.

1:10:36.620 --> 1:10:38.038
It worked.

1:10:38.956 --> 1:10:40.582
I got you.

1:10:41.041 --> 1:10:42.876
You don't waste time, do you?

1:10:45.170 --> 1:10:47.172
I don't have time to waste.

1:10:56.014 --> 1:10:57.975
Not your first rodeo.

1:10:58.100 --> 1:11:01.311
No. Hopefully my last.

1:11:12.281 --> 1:11:14.283
This is as far as we can go.

1:11:23.667 --> 1:11:27.254
This will be right here
when you get back.

1:11:28.630 --> 1:11:30.507
- OK.
- You be brave.

1:11:32.217 --> 1:11:33.427
OK?

1:11:34.094 --> 1:11:35.470
OK.

1:11:35.596 --> 1:11:37.264
You be brave.

1:11:53.530 --> 1:11:55.032
Who are these people?

1:11:56.366 --> 1:11:59.328
Families of people waiting
for transplants.

1:12:01.204 --> 1:12:02.998
They've got nowhere to go?

1:12:04.499 --> 1:12:05.792
No.

1:12:10.964 --> 1:12:13.050
- I hope it's not too hard.
- OK.

1:12:13.175 --> 1:12:15.886
- Someone's home.
- Daddy.

1:12:19.348 --> 1:12:21.016
You're looking at the new lieutenant.

1:12:21.141 --> 1:12:22.893
- Really?
- Hm-hmm.

1:12:23.602 --> 1:12:25.020
- Do you hear that?
- Daddy!

1:12:25.145 --> 1:12:26.521
- That's amazing!
- Thank you.

1:12:26.647 --> 1:12:28.232
- Daddy!
- Thank you.

1:12:28.357 --> 1:12:29.524
- Fire truck.
- Yes.

1:12:29.650 --> 1:12:32.569
Wow! Look at this. This is art.

1:12:32.694 --> 1:12:34.821
- This is amazing.
- It's not a fire truck.

1:12:34.947 --> 1:12:38.033
- It's not a fire truck, you're right.
- I'm gonna go run his bath.

1:12:38.158 --> 1:12:39.159
OK.

1:12:40.327 --> 1:12:42.913
- I am so proud of you.
- Thank you.

1:12:43.747 --> 1:12:45.165
This is fine.

1:12:45.916 --> 1:12:48.126
Hey? I wanna look at you.

1:12:48.252 --> 1:12:50.754
Oh! Come here.

1:12:52.547 --> 1:12:53.674
I love fire trucks.

1:12:53.799 --> 1:12:56.134
Yeah, I love fire trucks, too, huh?

1:12:57.678 --> 1:13:01.265
Don't you dare say it.

1:13:01.390 --> 1:13:02.808
I won't say it.

1:13:02.933 --> 1:13:04.017
- Say it.
- Say it?

1:13:04.142 --> 1:13:05.352
- Yeah.
- Fire truck.

1:13:05.477 --> 1:13:08.689
Oh!

1:13:14.570 --> 1:13:16.280
<i>So, here's the thing.</i>

1:13:19.116 --> 1:13:21.743
<i>That's not what really happened.</i>

1:13:27.708 --> 1:13:28.959
<i>It would have been nice.</i>

1:13:30.919 --> 1:13:32.671
<i>Hmm, it would
have been more than nice.</i>

1:13:36.091 --> 1:13:37.467
<i>Perfect wife.</i>

1:13:40.387 --> 1:13:41.930
<i>Perfect family.</i>

1:13:44.474 --> 1:13:45.893
<i>All I could ever want.</i>

1:13:48.020 --> 1:13:49.229
<i>And more.</i>

1:13:57.571 --> 1:14:00.616
<i>But it turns out life had
something else in store for me.</i>

1:14:55.295 --> 1:14:57.756
<i>They ran every test
you can imagine on me.</i>

1:14:59.341 --> 1:15:02.511
<i>CT, MRI, blood,</i>

1:15:02.636 --> 1:15:04.555
<i>oxygen levels, the works.</i>

1:15:05.597 --> 1:15:07.391
<i>And everything seemed to be fine.</i>

1:15:07.516 --> 1:15:09.601
<i>Except for one little thing.</i>

1:15:12.479 --> 1:15:13.981
Doctor.

1:15:15.065 --> 1:15:19.027
The MRI shows bleeding
in the frontal lobe of your son's brain.

1:15:19.152 --> 1:15:20.529
There is no sign of trauma,

1:15:20.654 --> 1:15:23.532
so it's possible he may have
some type of aneurism

1:15:23.657 --> 1:15:26.451
or a bleeding arterial
venous malformation.

1:15:26.577 --> 1:15:28.453
English, please.

1:15:28.579 --> 1:15:32.082
It's basically a leaking blood vessel.

1:15:34.501 --> 1:15:36.295
So, what's next?

1:15:36.420 --> 1:15:39.715
We're planning to drain some fluid
and relieve the pressure on his brain.

1:15:39.840 --> 1:15:42.342
I don't understand.
He was perfectly healthy.

1:15:42.467 --> 1:15:44.177
We just saw him last week.

1:15:44.303 --> 1:15:47.431
About two percent of the population
have this kind of issue

1:15:47.556 --> 1:15:48.724
and never even know it.

1:15:48.849 --> 1:15:52.102
Even if it leaks,
it's not necessarily fatal.

1:15:53.353 --> 1:15:56.648
- Most of the time, it isn't.
- What do you mean, most of the time?

1:15:56.773 --> 1:15:59.067
He just looks like he's sleeping.

1:15:59.192 --> 1:16:00.611
We'll know more in the morning.

1:16:00.736 --> 1:16:03.238
In the meantime,
you should all get some rest.

1:16:03.363 --> 1:16:05.115
There's a hotel down the street.

1:16:15.083 --> 1:16:17.002
Chris, listen to me.

1:16:17.127 --> 1:16:18.921
It's Dad.

1:16:21.131 --> 1:16:22.716
I love you, son.

1:16:25.010 --> 1:16:28.680
Now, put your hand in God's hand, OK?

1:16:29.431 --> 1:16:31.058
Put your hand in God's hand.

1:16:59.586 --> 1:17:01.505
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

1:17:01.630 --> 1:17:03.090
We should talk.

1:17:18.981 --> 1:17:23.527
Christopher's condition
has seriously deteriorated overnight.

1:17:26.405 --> 1:17:28.448
I'm afraid
there's no other way to say this.

1:17:29.366 --> 1:17:31.243
This is death.

1:17:31.952 --> 1:17:37.249
We have to do one last test on him
to verify that he is braindead.

1:17:39.960 --> 1:17:42.129
<i>Then we will take him off
all of the machines.</i>

1:17:47.968 --> 1:17:49.386
<i>I'm so sorry.</i>

1:18:02.608 --> 1:18:05.068
<i>Can we wait until
his brother John gets here?</i>

1:18:05.903 --> 1:18:07.404
<i>Yes, of course.</i>

1:18:09.823 --> 1:18:11.742
<i>We can wait until you're ready.</i>

1:18:44.733 --> 1:18:46.902
We can't actually allow for this.

1:18:47.611 --> 1:18:49.821
They're gonna give parts of him away.

1:18:50.322 --> 1:18:51.782
Like a junked car?

1:18:52.157 --> 1:18:54.701
- Honey.
- No, I'm not OK with this.

1:18:55.244 --> 1:18:56.912
Mom, you can't agree to this, can you?

1:18:57.037 --> 1:18:58.580
It's what he wanted.

1:19:48.338 --> 1:19:50.132
Hey, big little brother.

1:19:52.676 --> 1:19:57.222
Usually, every time we're alone,
you do most of the talking.

1:19:59.725 --> 1:20:01.643
I'm not used to this.

1:20:03.270 --> 1:20:05.814
Where's your wisecrack jokes
when I need them, huh?

1:20:07.524 --> 1:20:09.484
I know I give you a hard time...

1:20:10.444 --> 1:20:11.820
most of the time.

1:20:13.405 --> 1:20:16.700
"Work harder, study stronger."

1:20:18.285 --> 1:20:20.245
What does it even matter now, huh?

1:20:26.752 --> 1:20:28.128
I am sorry...

1:20:29.588 --> 1:20:31.423
for so many things.

1:20:33.967 --> 1:20:35.010
You know, it's...

1:20:35.886 --> 1:20:37.679
You know, it's because I love you.

1:20:38.222 --> 1:20:39.514
Right?

1:20:41.016 --> 1:20:42.267
Chris...

1:20:44.061 --> 1:20:45.479
Look, I need you to hear me.

1:20:47.648 --> 1:20:49.233
I love you.

1:20:52.945 --> 1:20:54.446
And I'm proud...

1:20:56.156 --> 1:20:57.783
proud to be your big brother.

1:21:02.079 --> 1:21:03.080
Bye, buddy.

1:21:15.425 --> 1:21:19.680
Mr. Gregory, there are planes
flying all over the country tonight

1:21:19.805 --> 1:21:21.557
because of your boy.

1:21:21.682 --> 1:21:26.103
We have matches for
all the abdominal and thoracic organs.

1:21:26.228 --> 1:21:30.023
Heart, lungs, liver, pancreas,

1:21:30.607 --> 1:21:32.818
kidneys, and eyes.

1:21:33.443 --> 1:21:36.613
Your son is saving five lives.

1:21:36.738 --> 1:21:38.365
Will we, uh...

1:21:39.825 --> 1:21:41.743
Will we ever find out who they are?

1:21:43.787 --> 1:21:45.122
<i>Maybe someday.</i>

1:21:46.582 --> 1:21:48.125
<i>Who knows?</i>

1:21:48.250 --> 1:21:49.835
<i>Maybe you'll get a letter.</i>

1:21:51.044 --> 1:21:52.379
<i>Maybe not.</i>

1:21:54.965 --> 1:21:58.886
<i>Sometimes folks write,
sometimes families meet.</i>

1:22:01.263 --> 1:22:02.973
<i>It isn't easy.</i>

1:22:03.098 --> 1:22:04.558
<i>But it can happen.</i>

1:22:05.851 --> 1:22:09.104
<i>Only through the agency, though.
No names or addresses are shared.</i>

1:22:09.229 --> 1:22:11.273
<i>Just general age, sex, and location.</i>

1:22:11.398 --> 1:22:14.818
<i>But... I wouldn't expect too much.</i>

1:22:15.694 --> 1:22:17.863
<i>They've all been fighting
their own battles.</i>

1:22:20.240 --> 1:22:21.950
<i>Thank you.</i>

1:22:24.411 --> 1:22:25.787
Thank you.

1:23:08.247 --> 1:23:10.249
Thank you so much for being here.

1:23:12.501 --> 1:23:15.420
My family and I appreciate
your prayers for Chris.

1:23:16.546 --> 1:23:19.758
If there's anything
you could do for us, it's, uh...

1:23:20.509 --> 1:23:21.718
it's this.

1:23:28.392 --> 1:23:30.269
Before you go to sleep tonight,

1:23:33.230 --> 1:23:35.357
please call someone you love
and tell them.

1:23:40.028 --> 1:23:41.613
Call a friend.

1:23:43.532 --> 1:23:46.034
Or a relative
you haven't talked to in a while.

1:24:01.174 --> 1:24:04.469
And don't ask them about
their grades or their cellphone bill.

1:24:09.641 --> 1:24:11.268
Just tell them...

1:24:12.394 --> 1:24:13.896
how much you love them.

1:24:17.441 --> 1:24:19.443
Thank you all for coming.

1:24:19.568 --> 1:24:20.986
Thank you.

1:24:53.393 --> 1:24:54.770
I'm alive.

1:24:58.523 --> 1:25:00.609
I'm alive. I'm...

1:25:03.237 --> 1:25:04.821
I'm alive.

1:25:07.991 --> 1:25:10.619
Who's... who's in here breathing for me?

1:25:11.161 --> 1:25:14.206
An angel. That's all we know.

1:25:22.965 --> 1:25:24.299
OK.

1:25:26.093 --> 1:25:28.053
OK.

1:25:33.892 --> 1:25:35.185
Yes.

1:26:35.495 --> 1:26:39.708
The souls of the righteous
are in the hand of God.

1:26:40.292 --> 1:26:42.294
And no torment shall touch them.

1:26:44.504 --> 1:26:46.632
In the eyes of the foolish,

1:26:47.257 --> 1:26:48.467
they seem to have died,

1:26:49.384 --> 1:26:53.513
their departure
thought to be an affliction

1:26:53.639 --> 1:26:55.641
and their going from us
to be their destruction.

1:26:55.766 --> 1:26:58.393
But they are at peace.

1:27:01.688 --> 1:27:04.858
For though, in the sight of men,
they were punished,

1:27:04.983 --> 1:27:07.778
their hope is full of immortality.

1:27:26.922 --> 1:27:30.300
I will always love you.

1:28:34.281 --> 1:28:35.240
Oh.

1:28:35.365 --> 1:28:36.950
The nurses are calling him Superman.

1:28:37.868 --> 1:28:39.494
No one can believe
how well you're recovering.

1:28:39.620 --> 1:28:41.580
I feel half my age, Doctor.

1:28:42.456 --> 1:28:44.041
Who was he?

1:28:44.166 --> 1:28:46.919
I can't release
that kind of information.

1:28:47.044 --> 1:28:49.713
We need to know. Please.

1:28:50.631 --> 1:28:54.676
I will check with the organ agency
and see what they'll release.

1:28:54.801 --> 1:28:57.721
But I think we should
get you home first.

1:29:04.728 --> 1:29:06.063
Thank you.

1:29:06.188 --> 1:29:07.481
You're welcome.

1:29:30.712 --> 1:29:32.631
It's handwritten, and, uh...

1:29:32.756 --> 1:29:35.676
they blacked out his name
and his signature.

1:29:36.635 --> 1:29:38.095
Read it.

1:29:44.518 --> 1:29:46.853
"To whoever and his family.

1:29:46.979 --> 1:29:49.898
I understand I am
the recipient of a gift

1:29:50.023 --> 1:29:53.360
from a relative of yours
that is beyond repayment.

1:29:57.823 --> 1:30:01.076
I cannot imagine the grief
caused by your loss

1:30:01.201 --> 1:30:07.291
and there are no words anyone can say
or write to extinguish that pain.

1:30:09.668 --> 1:30:15.632
Nevertheless, you have shared with me
the grandest gift I will ever receive.

1:30:17.009 --> 1:30:18.552
The gift of life."

1:30:52.586 --> 1:30:53.754
Grace.

1:30:53.879 --> 1:30:55.297
Honey, come here.

1:30:56.757 --> 1:30:57.841
What?

1:30:58.550 --> 1:30:59.676
Uh...

1:31:00.636 --> 1:31:02.888
They gave Christopher a name.

1:31:03.013 --> 1:31:04.598
What is it?

1:31:05.390 --> 1:31:06.850
Gabriel.

1:31:08.560 --> 1:31:11.730
The archangel of new life
and incarnation.

1:31:12.773 --> 1:31:13.690
Our boy.

1:31:14.858 --> 1:31:16.235
Their angel.

1:31:16.818 --> 1:31:18.362
Gabriel.

1:31:51.770 --> 1:31:54.481
Gabriel was
their 19-year-old son Christopher.

1:31:55.607 --> 1:31:57.818
He was in love with a girl named Sam.

1:32:01.613 --> 1:32:03.282
The parents lost their son

1:32:03.865 --> 1:32:05.826
and she lost her love.

1:32:08.287 --> 1:32:10.205
He was just a boy, you know.

1:32:14.835 --> 1:32:16.545
He was just a boy.

1:33:58.146 --> 1:33:59.481
Chris is here.

1:34:00.107 --> 1:34:01.775
He's with me.

1:34:13.453 --> 1:34:15.205
I'm going to take good care of him.

1:34:15.831 --> 1:34:17.124
Thank you.

1:34:23.797 --> 1:34:25.382
- Hi.
- Hi. I'm Grace.

1:34:25.507 --> 1:34:26.675
Hi.

1:34:27.217 --> 1:34:28.719
Nice to meet you.

1:34:58.624 --> 1:35:01.376
<i>Go ahead, take my eyes.</i>

1:35:01.501 --> 1:35:03.086
<i>They're no use to me now.</i>

1:35:03.921 --> 1:35:06.798
<i>But just know that when they look
at some little children playing,</i>

1:35:06.924 --> 1:35:08.634
<i>I'll be smiling with them.</i>

1:35:11.136 --> 1:35:14.306
<i>Take my heart so someone else
can live and love and...</i>

1:35:15.182 --> 1:35:19.228
<i>with this gift, know that my love
remains in this world.</i>

1:35:22.814 --> 1:35:25.400
<i>Take my lungs so someone else can sing.</i>

1:35:26.652 --> 1:35:29.947
<i>And if you listen carefully,
you'll hear that I'm singing with them.</i>

1:35:43.168 --> 1:35:47.172
<i>I'm sorry I didn't have more hugs
to give and jokes to tell.</i>

1:35:48.590 --> 1:35:50.717
<i>I did my best to make others smile.</i>

1:35:53.011 --> 1:35:57.057
<i>And when I die, I won't be here.</i>

1:35:58.267 --> 1:35:59.810
<i>I'll be everywhere.</i>

1:36:12.864 --> 1:36:14.324
<i>So, that's my story.</i>

1:36:14.449 --> 1:36:17.452
<i>And it didn't happen the way
any of us would have expected.</i>

1:36:18.495 --> 1:36:20.163
<i>But it was a miracle.</i>

1:36:20.914 --> 1:36:23.792
<i>Beautiful, awesome and fantastic.</i>
